opennlp.ccg.util
Class DelegatedFilter<E,D>

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.util.DelegatedFilter<E,D>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of elements that this filter applies to.
D - The type of elements that the delegated filter applies to.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Filter<E>
public abstract class DelegatedFilter<E,D>
extends Object
implements Filter<E>

Abstract class for filters that delegates to another filter that tests elements that do not necessarily apply to the same type of elements as this filter. This filter's allows(Object) method returns the value of the delegate filter's allows(...) method for the value returned by delegateValueFor(Object) for the specified element.

Concrete subclasses need to specify (1) the delegate filter (via their constructor), and (2) a way to determine which element of type D the delegate filter should use based on a specified element of type E by implementing delegateValueFor(Object). A typical example is the case when a filter is desired that compares elements of type E, but the comparison needs to take place on some type-D object somehow derived from instances of E, e.g. by an accessor method.

Author:
Scott Martin
